hands_on_practices.problem:
Consider the function $f: \mathbb{R} \to \mathbb{R}$ defined as follows:
$$
f(x) = \begin{cases}
x^2  \text{if } x \in \mathbb{Q} \\
2x - 1  \text{if } x \in \mathbb{R} \setminus \mathbb{Q}
\end{cases}
$$
where $\mathbb{Q}$ denotes the set of rational numbers and $\mathbb{R}$ denotes the set of real numbers. Determine all points $c \in \mathbb{R}$ at which the function $f$ is continuous.
